# Privacy Policy

## Introduction
Welcome to **Pray & Progress**! Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting your personal information. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our app.

## Information We Collect
When you sign up for **Pray & Progress**, we collect the following information:
- **Email Address**: Used to create and manage your account.
- **Username**: Your chosen display name within the app.

Additionally, habit data (such as completion statuses and habit tracking) is stored in our remote database to provide you with the ability to track your progress across devices.

## How We Use Your Information
The information we collect is used solely to provide and improve the app experience:
- **Email Address and Username**: To manage your account and provide access to your habit data across devices.
- **Habit Data**: Stored remotely to track your progress and allow seamless usage on multiple devices.

We do not use your information for any other purposes such as marketing or advertising.

## Sharing Your Information
We do **not** share your personal information (email, username, or habit data) with third parties. All data is securely stored and accessible only by you through the app.

## Your Rights
As a user of **Pray & Progress**, you have full control over your account and data. You can update or delete your email, username, or habits directly within the app. If you wish to delete your account entirely, please contact us.

## Data Security
We use appropriate security measures to protect your data stored in our remote database, ensuring your information remains safe from unauthorized access.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify or update this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be reflected in the updated version of **Pray & Progress** available for download.

## Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or the app, please contact us at **abdullaha6@gmail.com**.
